node.text: Exactly 1 year ago, I scored my 1st ever Pole Position on a Formula 1 Race Week-End. I miss the feeling of driving an F1 car and I really hope the situation will improve very soon. Stay safe and hope to share other moments like this one very soon ❤️

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Charles Leclerc in Hungaroring.

node.text: Luck hasn't been on our side for the first half of the season and it definitely wasn't today. Huge shame as it was a big opportunity.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Charles Leclerc in Hungaroring. May be an image of one or more people.

node.text: A bit disappointed as qualifying is really important here. We're not too far away in P7 but overtaking is going to be tricky tomorrow.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Charles Leclerc in Hungaroring.

node.text:
Friday Done ! 
Looking forward to tomorrow 🔥

node.text: A day later and I'm still 50% happy and 50% disappointed, but that's a good thing. It's amazing to be back on the podium and it shows the progress we have made but it also shows that there's still some way to go. I'm so proud of the hard work everyone is doing @scuderiaferrari. We'll keep fighting and we'll be back on top soon 👊

node.text: Ahhhhhhhh, incredibly close. I gave absolutely everything to win this race but lost out in the last two laps. The biggest victory today though is to see Max safe after that big crash. Now onto Hungary, thank you for the support ❤️

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Charles Leclerc in Silverstone with @andferrari007. May be an image of 1 person and standing.

node.text: Really enjoyed that !! P4 with a strong pace, will push to convert that into a good main race tomorrow 🔥

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Charles Leclerc in Silverstone. May be an image of outdoors and text that says 'RICHARD MILLE වලn kaspersky'.

node.text: P4 in qualifying! Great start to the weekend but there's a lot of racing still to come with the sprint tomorrow.

node.text: 70 years since the first ever @scuderiaferrari win. Every day we're working for the next one.
